result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Cases  called at 1:59 PM: 21CF901, 21CF1320, 21CF1374, 21CF1390, 22CF372, 22CF374.
Defendant Emily E. Voorhies in court in custody with Attorney Robert Allen Thorson. Attorney Matthew Z Kirkpatrick in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Agreement has been reached. Victim/Witness statute complied with. Defendant is advised of charges, maximum penalties, elements of the crime(s) and constitutional rights. 
21CF1374: Defendant pleads No Contest to Count 2: Misdemeanor Retail Theft-Intentionally Take (<=$500);Repeater.
21CF901: Defendant pleads No Contest to Count 1: Identity Theft-Avoidance; Repeater and Count 4: Retail Theft-Intentionally Conceal (<=$500);Repeater; PTAC. Repeaters acknowledged.
21CF1390: Defendant pleads No Contest to Count 3: Felony Bail Jumping; Repeater.

Sentence is Withheld and the Defendant is placed on 3 Years of Probation (on the felonies only) with the following conditions:
AODA and follow through with recommendations. Maintain absolute sobriety. Any conditions, programming or treatment per the agent and follow through with recommendations. 
No contact with K.N. any Woodman's location, any Wal-Mart location, No contact with any known drug dealers/users except in a therapeutic setting. 
Court Costs/surcharges, DNA sample/surcharge.

Defendant is sentenced to Court Costs/surcharges, DNA sample/surcharge on the Misdemeanors (Count 4 in 21CF901 and Count 2 in 21CF1374).
Defendant is granted 35 days of credit in 21CF901 and 34 days of credit in 21CF1374 and 21CF1390.
Remaining charges are dismissed and read in.
